data.description: ***** BUYER'S AGENT COMMISSIONS HONORED****It is like living in a beautiful park. Two of our live oak trees made the list of the biggest and oldest during the Beaufort 300 Year Celebration. It has 3 bedrooms and 2 1/2 Baths (Zillow claims 3, but it is 2 1/2). It has a studio in the back that COULD be used as a garage with additional space for a studio or storage. Walk past only 2 houses and you are in our gorgeous Pigeon Point Park. Walk a few blocks to the USCB Center for the Arts. There are several restaurants within a few blocks for an easy walk to lunch or dinner. It is an easy walk to downtown and the waterfront park and all that Beaufort has to offer. It is wonderful. Call 843-321-9623.
data.whatILove: Everything! It's proximity to downtown - totally walkable. It's proximity to Pigeon Point Park! It's contemporary design based on the Historic cruciform shape of a traditional Beaufort Home. The TREES. The saltwater pool with it's electric cover! It is like living in a small forest in the middle of downtown! Call 843-321-9623.
